<body>

<h1>Uppu Seedai</h1>

<main class="recipe-details">
    <!-- Image Section -->
    <img src="path_to_your_image.jpg" alt="Uppu Seedai" class="recipe-image">

    <!-- Ingredients Section -->
    <div class="ingredients">
        <h2>Ingredients</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>1 cup rice flour</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons urad dal flour (optional)</li>
            <li>2 tablespoons grated coconut (fresh or desiccated)</li>
            <li>1 tablespoon melted ghee</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon sesame seeds</li>
            <li>1 teaspoon cumin seeds</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon asafoetida (hing)</li>
            <li>1/2 teaspoon salt</li>
            <li>Water, as needed</li>
            <li>Oil, for deep frying</li>
        </ul>
    </div>

    <!-- Procedure Section -->
    <div class="procedure">
        <h2>Procedure</h2>
        <ul>
            <li>In a mixing bowl, combine rice flour, urad dal flour (if using), grated coconut, melted ghee, sesame seeds, cumin seeds, asafoetida, and salt.</li>
            <li>Add water gradually and knead the mixture into a smooth dough. The dough should be firm yet pliable.</li>
            <li>Divide the dough into small lemon-sized balls and roll them between your palms to make smooth balls.</li>
            <li>Place the balls on a clean, dry cloth or kitchen towel and let them air dry for about 20-30 minutes. This helps in preventing the seedai from bursting while frying.</li>
            <li>Heat oil in a deep frying pan over medium heat.</li>
            <li>Gently slide a few seedai balls into the hot oil and fry them until they turn golden brown and crispy. Make sure not to overcrowd the pan.</li>
            <li>Remove the fried seedai using a slotted spoon and drain excess oil on a paper towel.</li>
            <li>Repeat the frying process with the remaining seedai balls.</li>
            <li>Once cooled, store the uppu seedai in an airtight container. They stay fresh for a couple of weeks.</li>
            <li>Serve and enjoy the crispy and savory Uppu Seedai as a snack!</li>
        </ul>
    </div>
</main>

